The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Nation | Toy train derails
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                     Toy train derails
          OUR CORRESPONDENT                              
	Shimla, Dec. 21: A toy train derailed near Shimla, killing one tourist on the spot and injuring six, two of whom were from Bengal.        
	The Shimla-bound holiday special derailed at Dharampur, 62km from Shimla. Two bogies and the engine of the train slipped from the rails. One passenger died on the spot, said Amandeep Garg, the deputy commissioner of police, Solan, under which Dharapur falls.        
	The accident happened near tunnel number 20 around 8.30am, Garg added.        
	Vandana Pandey, who was seriously injured, has been admitted to PGI hospital in Chandigarh.         
	Eighteen-year-old Jhilika Dass and 17-year-old Sadhna Dass from Bengal were also injured.        
	The cause of the accident is not known. Weve ordered an inquiry. Traffic on the Kalka-Shimla railway line has been suspended and will resume on Monday, said H.K. Jaggi, the divisional railway manager, Ambala.                                                                                                                                                                          
